{
  "texts": [
    "with θ fixed at an estimate of some central posterior value (e.g.",
    "the posterior mean).",
    "The value of σ2 N can also be used to trigger updating of N, for example, if σ2 N > 1.5.",
    "We refer the reader to Botha et al. (2023b) for further discussion, noting their critique that, in the SMC 2 setting, this approach can be sensitive to the initial value of N.",
    "However, and as discussed at the beginning of this section, p (θ) enkf,t (y 0:t |x 1:N 0:t) is likely to be less sensitive to N than the corresponding particle filter estimator."
